===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Thornburg had 45 residents, 22 households, and 17 families.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A77835&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A77835&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref> The [[population density]] was 226.0 inhabitants per square mile (87.3/km<sup>2</sup>), and there were 24 housing units at an average density of 120.5 per square mile (46.5/km<sup>2</sup>).<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A77835&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 2, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref> Of these housing units, 8.3% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

Of the 22 households, 45.5% had children under the age of 18 living in them, 68.2% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 4.5% were cohabitating couples, 13.6% had a female householder with no spouse or partner present, and 13.6% had a male householder with no spouse or partner present.<ref name="Census2020DP"/> 22.7% of households were non-families, 18.2% were made up of individuals, and 13.6% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

The median age was 46.8 years. 17.8% of residents were under age 20, 2.2% were from 20 to 24, 26.7% were from 25 to 44, 35.6% were from 45 to 64, and 17.8% were 65 or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/> The population was 55.6% male and 44.4% female; for every 100 females, there were 125.0 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 164.3 males.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

